},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَدِقّ","in_corpus":true,"count":4,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَدِقّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"دَقَقْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"دَقَقْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":27,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12783"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to crush, to bruise"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grind, to pulverize, to powder"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to knock, to drive in (door, wedge, nail, bell so it resounds etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be become thin, fine, little, small"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be insignificant, unimportant"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be subtle for perception"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَقَّ (daqqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12783","headword_ar":"دَقَّ","root":"dq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadiq~u","text_ar":"يَدِقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dif~apN","text_ar":"دِفَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daqiyq","text_ar":"دَقِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contr."},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiyZ","text_ar":"غَلِيظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astdq~","text_ar":"استدقّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, thin"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small in diameter or circumference as compared with length:"},{"kind":"text","text":"also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small in all dimensions; small in size; minute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a whole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its component particles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes, as said of a garment or the like,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine, as opposed to thick"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raq~a","text_ar":"رَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galuZa","text_ar":"غَلُظَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astdq~","text_ar":"استدقّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hilaAl","text_ar":"هِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or moon a little after or before the change], and of other things. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riq~apN","text_ar":"رِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  And [hence], aor. and inf. n. as above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, little in estimation, paltry, inconsiderable, mean, vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contemptible."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says to him who refuses to confer a benefit,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~a bika","text_ar":"دَقَّ بِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluquka","text_ar":"خُلُقُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural disposition, hath rendered thee mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; the verb being made trans. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with a common usage mentioned in p. 141]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, [aor. and] inf. n. as above, said of a thing, an affair, or a case, [and of speech, or language,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, subtile, nice, abstruse, recondite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~a fiY kalaAmihi","text_ar":"دَقَّ فِى كَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, subtile, nice, abstruse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~ahu","text_ar":"دَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~N","text_ar":"دَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crushed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bruised, brayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pounded, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he beat it with a thing so that he broke it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crushed it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: *) namely, a thing, (S, M, TA,) such as medicine, &c. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He beat it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a garment or the like; in washing and whitening it. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~a AlbaAba","text_ar":"دَقَّ البَابَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knocked at the door"},{"kind":"text","text":"for admission.] ―         -b3-  And [hence also, (in the CK, erroneously, “ or, ”) as appears from what follows,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it apparent; showed, exhibited, manifested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revealed, it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so says IAar, citing the following verse of Zuheyr:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tadaArakotumaA EabosFA wa*uboyaAna baEodamaA\n                      \n                     \n                        tafaAnawoA wadaq~uwA bayonahumo EiTora mano$imi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye two repaired the condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the tribes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of 'Abs and Dhubyán"},{"kind":"text","text":"by peace, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaAfayotumaA","text_ar":"تَلَافَيْتُمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorahumaA biAlS~uloHi","text_ar":"اَمْرَهُمَا بِالصُّلْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after they had shared, one with another, in destruction, and had brayed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among themselves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the perfume of Menshim"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a sign of their having leagued together against their enemy; i. e., after slaughter had come upon the last of their men, as upon the last of those who perfumed themselves with the perfume of Menshim: for [it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn$m","text_ar":"منشم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of a woman who sold perfume in Mekkeh, and a party bought of her some perfume, and leagued together to fight their enemy, making the dipping of their hands in that perfume to be a sign of their league; and they fought until they were slain to the last of them: whence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oA^amu mino EiTori mano$ima","text_ar":"اَشْاَمُ مِنْ عِطْرِ مَنْشِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (EM p. 117:) [so that, accord. to this explanation, which is one of many,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn$m","text_ar":"منشم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made perfectly decl. for the sake of the rhyme:] or the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after they had manifested enmities and faults."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says also, in cases of enmity,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aduq~an~a $uEuwraka","text_ar":"لَاَدُقَّنَّ شُعُورَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly manifest thy circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duq~a","text_ar":"دُقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~N","text_ar":"دَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diq~N","text_ar":"دِقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was seized with the malady termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diq~","text_ar":"دِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hectic fever"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (MA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","M","TA"]}]}}